This paper discusses the use of network slicing and machine learning for V2X services in 5G networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes the use of ML algorithms for automated network operation, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of network slicing, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of multi-dimensional network resources, which could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory).
